<biogHist>
<abstract>The Widows' Pension was a Commonwealth allowance introduced to enable widows with dependent children to stay at home and look after them, rather than having to go out to work to keep the family from destitution. From October 1942 until 1976, the Widows' Pension was exempt from income tax. Unmarried mothers, de facto wives and wives who had left their husbands were not eligible for the Widows' Pension.</abstract>

</biogHist>
